Write a function called list_starts_with_a that takes in lst as a parameter and returns a new list with the words from lst that start with “a”. 
For example, list_starts_with_a(["alphabet", "apple", "banana", "coding", "amazing"]) would return ["alphabet", "apple", "amazing"].

def list_starts_with_a(lst):
    ls = []
    for item in lst:
        if item.startswith("a"):
            ls.append(item)
    return ls
            
print(list_starts_with_a(["alphabet", "apple", "banana", "coding", "amazing"]))

